model.documentation: The Open Group Architecture Framework - Government Reference Model

element.name: State Governance
element.documentation: The Governance Business Service

element.name: State Governance
element.documentation: The Governance Role

element.name: State Action
element.documentation: The Governance Function

element.name: International Affairs and Trade
element.documentation: International Affairs and Trade consists of activities undertaken by the government to facilitate financial support and trade with international economies and related to the conduct and implementation of policies, aid programs, treaties, and diplomatic relations.

element.name: Development and Aid
element.documentation: Function that aid development and provide humanitarian assistance to less developed economies.

element.name: International Development
element.documentation: Comprises activities that aid development to developing economies through voluntary transfer of goods and services.

element.name: Humanitarian Aid
element.documentation: Refers to activities that support less developed economies in order to facilitate growth and recovery from conflict.

element.name: Trade
element.documentation: Function to increase prosperity through enabling overseas trade.

element.name: Global Trade
element.documentation: Pertains to activities undertaken to increase economic wealth by enabling trade overseas and facilitating the movement of goods and services.

element.name: Export Control
element.documentation: Regulates the international sale and movement of goods from the country and ensures compliance with domestic and international protocols and guidelines.

element.name: Import Control
element.documentation: Regulates the international purchase and movement of goods into the country and ensures compliance with domestic and international protocols and guidelines.

element.name: International Affairs
element.documentation: Services that maintain international relationships by providing overseas diplomatic advice and negotiating partnerships and agreements.

element.name: Foreign Affairs
element.documentation: Refers to international contributions by providing diplomatic assistance and conducting consultations with international governments.

element.name: Foreign Treaties
element.documentation: Activities that maintain relationships with international governments by monitoring existing treaties and negotiating partnerships and formal agreements.

element.name: Defense and Security
element.documentation: Defense and Security corresponds to the research, maintenance, equipment, procurement, operations, and development of forces, weapons, and related entities. This also comprises remuneration and benefits paid to all active and non-active civilians and personnel.

element.name: Defense Activities
element.documentation: Programs leveraged by national defense that include defense-related activities, threat reduction, and counter-terrorism.

element.name: Counter-Terrorism
element.documentation: Includes domestic and international responses that correspond to the elimination and deterrence of acts of terrorism.

element.name: Military Operations
element.documentation: Corresponds to all miscellaneous defense-related events (e.g., expenses related to procurement external to national defense).

element.name: Threat Reduction
element.documentation: Corresponds to the activities to reduce and prevent the spread of goods or confidential data related to threats. This will include data exploitation, effective information maneuver, and cybersecurity operations.

element.name: Defense Readiness and Preparation
element.documentation: Maintenance, equipment, procurement, and development of forces, infrastructure, remuneration, and benefits paid to personnel.

element.name: Defense Application
element.documentation: Includes activities used to achieve defense objectives in all environments through amalgamation of the use of engagement and maneuver.

element.name: Defense Network and IT Infrastructure
element.documentation: Corresponds to the movement of information in order to satisfy the connectivity and interoperability needs of the defense.

element.name: Defense Training and Allocation
element.documentation: Corresponds to the improvement of individuals and collective performance within defense through real-life tasks and functions and simulated training environments to integrate the use of maneuver and engagement activities.

element.name: Population Protection
element.documentation: Includes all activities that ensure the security of and protect the general population, government, and leaders.

element.name: Intelligence and International Security
element.documentation: Activities to protect, analyze, and comprehend the needs and interests of the government and allies.

element.name: Intelligence and Counter-Intelligence Operations
element.documentation: Includes all activities that encompass the ability to analyze and comprehend the needs of the government and citizens.

element.name: Intelligence and Counter-Intelligence Operations
element.documentation: Includes all activities that encompass the ability to analyze and comprehend the needs of the government and citizens.

element.name: International Security Assistance
element.documentation: Corresponds to all activities used to protect the government’s interests and respond to potential threats by exploiting cross-governmental IT infrastructure, networks, and information.

element.name: Special Intelligence
element.documentation: Pertains to advanced services that process, analyze, and collect information in order to support national interests.

element.name: General Government and Local Services
element.documentation: General Government and Local Services involves the provision of general customer services and operations including registrations, licensing, applications, workforce planning, social services, management of labor rights, and local services.

element.name: Customer Services
element.documentation: Provides assistance and advice to the users of the services.

element.name: Business Licenses
element.documentation: The process associated with completing an application to initiate a business.

element.name: Cashiers
element.documentation: Refers to the provision of individuals who are responsible for dealing with incoming enquiries and oversee general clerical duties.

element.name: Front Desk
element.documentation: Encompasses the operation and co-ordination of individuals responsible for performing administrative duties.

element.name: Housing Gateway
element.documentation: Refers to the operation, eligibility, and application assessment of affordable housing purchase schemes.

element.name: Imports Administrations
element.documentation: Responsible for collection, preparation, and general enquiries regarding import documents for entry of shipments from abroad.

element.name: License Applications
element.documentation: Activities associated with the overall management and paperwork of the documented authority necessary to perform a regulated role.

element.name: People Hub
element.documentation: Oversees the hiring, administration, and training of staff within customer services and operations roles.

element.name: Registration Cards
element.documentation: Activities associated with the overall management and paperwork for individuals claiming asylum.

element.name: Social Security, Benefits, and Pensions
element.documentation: Refers to activities associated with queries, paperwork required in order to apply for a social security number, benefits and pension schemes, and potential discrepancies that may arise.

element.name: Student Finance
element.documentation: Encompasses the management and provision of student loans and grants to cover tuition fees and costs associated with undertaking higher education.

element.name: Tax Forms
element.documentation: Involves the support and provision of forms to taxpayers and tax-exempt organizations to report financial information.

element.name: Workforce Planning
element.documentation: Encompasses the analysis of the current and future workforce in order to identify gaps and enable the general government and local government to achieve strategic goals.

element.name: Customer Operations
element.documentation: The functions that directly engage the public.

element.name: Back to Work
element.documentation: Provides guidance, support, and information for individuals looking to return to work following a career break.

element.name: Benefits
element.documentation: Addresses provision and determination of eligibility for benefits including income-related benefits, housing benefits, child benefits, carer benefits, and disability benefits.

element.name: Benefits Fraud
element.documentation: Encompasses the conduct and investigation of individuals claiming benefits to which they are not entitled.

element.name: Customer Complaints
element.documentation: Includes the ability to assess and address individuals’ dissatisfaction with customer operations.

element.name: Income Support
element.documentation: Involves the provision of extra money to individuals on low incomes.

element.name: Pensions
element.documentation: Encompasses the distribution of fixed payments periodically to support citizens’ retirement from work.

element.name: Social Security Administration
element.documentation: Undertakes the responsibility for the assignment of social security numbers and administers social security retirement, survivors, and disability insurance programs.

element.name: Local Service
element.documentation: Provides services within a specific location or community.

element.name: Community Grants
element.documentation: The provision of grants and loans to community groups in order to fund local projects and services.

element.name: Community Planning and Consultation
element.documentation: Refers to the provision of information and recommendations to local community groups on budget and legal issues, and general advice on local projects and services.

element.name: Customer Forums
element.documentation: The provision of an online avenue used to integrate a community and share feedback.

element.name: Local Law
element.documentation: Provides advice and applies legal processes at town and area level.

element.name: Neighborhood Engagement and Development
element.documentation: Supports the establishment of local networks and activities, liaises with businesses to support community projects, and organizes activities for residents.

element.name: Superintendent Registrar
element.documentation: Oversees the registration of births, marriages, and deaths in the local community.

element.name: Young People and Education
element.documentation: Young People and Education comprises educational programs that correspond to early years, primary school, secondary school, higher education, and specialist schooling. This also includes children’s social services, safeguarding, and associated children and adolescent services; as well as skill or training activities undertaken by the government to promote education.

element.name: Children’s Service
element.documentation: Corresponds to social services, and additional safeguarding, adolescent support, and parental support in early years

element.name: Children and Adolescent Services
element.documentation: Provides support and guidance through a number of transition stages to adulthood.

element.name: Children’s Social Care and Safeguarding
element.documentation: Comprises safeguarding training, policies, and processes to ensure all children are protected from harm.

element.name: Early Years
element.documentation: Provides activities that support the learning, development, and care of children prior to entering schooling.

element.name: Family and Parenting
element.documentation: Includes activities to offer information and support to parents and carers to promote emotional wellbeing and positive family relationships.

element.name: Fostering and Adoption
element.documentation: The provision of temporary or long-term responsibility of a child to a surrogate parent.

element.name: Looked-after Children
element.documentation: Individuals in the care of local authorities as a result of mandatory care orders or parent agreements.

element.name: Curriculum
element.documentation: Outlines mandatory courses and units to be completed and communicates with departments to ensure consistency across education establishments.

element.name: Education
element.documentation: Includes the provisioning of skills and knowledge to children through schooling, education, and adherence to national expectations and standards.

element.name: Primary Schools
element.documentation: Consists of activities that provide education at an elementary level, with focus on reading and writing.

element.name: Secondary Schools
element.documentation: The provision of education through secondary-level educational establishments.

element.name: Specialist Teaching
element.documentation: Provides extra help, adapted programs or learning environments, specific equipment, or materials to support students.

element.name: Standards and Achievement
element.documentation: Comprises developing course materials, learning materials, resources, exam material, and exam administration that adhere to education standards and accredit education qualifications.

element.name: Apprenticeships
element.documentation: Consists of on-the-job training amalgamated with classroom training.

element.name: Early Careers
element.documentation: Includes the provision of training through workplace and traineeships.

element.name: Higher Education
element.documentation: Comprises education beyond secondary schooling.

element.name: Higher Education and Skills
element.documentation: Supports the provision of further education and training for work-related disciplines including apprenticeships, on-the-job training, and communications with industry and tertiary institutions.

element.name: Health and Community Wellbeing
element.documentation: Health and Community Wellbeing encompasses medical and nursing governance, strategy and care services provided to individuals and families, research and the provision of hospital and community services to safeguard mental and physical health.

element.name: Adult Mental Health
element.documentation: Provides access to psychological, employment support, trauma informed care, medicines management, and personalized support for adults with mental health needs.

element.name: Adult Safeguarding
element.documentation: Comprises safeguarding training, policies, and processes to ensure all adults are protected from harm.

element.name: Adult Social Care
element.documentation: Involves activities required in order to support adults with physical or learning difficulties.

element.name: Community Services
element.documentation: Involves protection of the physical and mental wellbeing of community members and monitoring community health services.

element.name: Counseling
element.documentation: Involves the use of talk therapy in order to support and assist adults with mental and emotional difficulties.

element.name: Emergency Services
element.documentation: The provision of pre-hospital care including ambulances, urgent response, and out of hospital treatment.

element.name: Facilities Management
element.documentation: Corresponds to the maintenance, management, and upkeep of hospital and community facilities.

element.name: Hospital and Community Services
element.documentation: The provision of services in order to safeguard the mental and physical health of adults.

element.name: Hospital Inpatients
element.documentation: The provision of hospital care and supervision for patients for at least one night.

element.name: Hospital Outpatients
element.documentation: The provision of hospital care and supervision for patients for less than one night.

element.name: Medical Allied Professions
element.documentation: Refers to the provision of diagnostic, technical, therapeutic, and support services by registered or qualified healthcare professionals.

element.name: Preventative Health
element.documentation: Refers to care provisioned in order to prevent illnesses or diseases.

element.name: Psychotherapy
element.documentation: Involves the use of physiological methods to support and assist adults with mental and emotional difficulties.

element.name: Information and Strategy Governance
element.documentation: Refers to the alignment of medical professionals, processes, tools, and technologies to achieve results.

element.name: Litigation
element.documentation: Refers to any disagreements/legal action taken against medical parties in the public sector.

element.name: Medical
element.documentation: Includes type, classification, and/or specialization of healthcare.

element.name: Medical Professional Lead
element.documentation: Refers to the service that sets the direction for medical practices and healthcare professionals.

element.name: Mortality
element.documentation: Refers to services and information related to a death and bereavement.

element.name: Pharmacy
element.documentation: Services that are conducted to prescribe, dispense, and distribute medication.

element.name: Primary Care Strategy
element.documentation: Provides the direction and framework for future primary care.

element.name: Regulatory Oversight
element.documentation: Refers to services used to co-ordinate functions that ensure policy is implemented consistently.

element.name: Health and Community Nursing
element.documentation: Manages care of the community, health, and leads teams of district nurses, community nurses, and support workers.

element.name: Nursing
element.documentation: The provision of services related to the care of the sick and infirm.

element.name: Nursing Standards and QA
element.documentation: Comprises activities used to evaluate standards of patient care and professional capabilities of nurses.

element.name: Nursing Strategy and Governance
element.documentation: Refers to the alignment of nursing services, processes, tools, and technologies to achieve results.

element.name: Judiciary, Justice, and Home Affairs
element.documentation: Judiciary, Justice, and Home Affairs covers the total cost of judiciary, prosecution, expenses connected with funding protection, law enforcement services, and the cost of criminal justice including incarceration, supervision, parole, and rehabilitation of prisoners.

element.name: Customs
element.documentation: Used to check for illegal goods or goods for which a tax may be applicable, and advises on quotas and customs regulations including inspections, cargo clearance, screen, and search.

element.name: Emergency Planning
element.documentation: Provides urgent assistance in unforeseen circumstances including emergency funding, logistical support, advises on equipment regulations, and co-ordinates government and community-based services.

element.name: Fire Service
element.documentation: Enables the provision of fire fighters and assistance to extinguish fires, minimize damage, promote fire safety, and enable emergency prevention, protection, and response.

element.name: Health and Safety
element.documentation: Consists of activities used to design, develop, and implement health and safety programs.

element.name: Immigration
element.documentation: Monitors the status of incoming travelers from overseas to the country to confirm that they are permitted to enter, and ensures on-arrival clearance through the passenger entry control system.

element.name: Police Service
element.documentation: Comprises activities that advise on rules and regulations, improve public safety, and reduce violence and use of illegal substances.

element.name: Protection and Law Enforcement
element.documentation: Refers to services that protect and safeguard the public and ensure compulsory compliance regarding the law.

element.name: Criminal Compensation
element.documentation: Encompasses programs that reimburse victims of crime for expenses related to the crime.

element.name: Criminal Justice
element.documentation: Encompasses the delivery of justice to individuals who have committed crimes and includes the provision of prosecution lawyers.

element.name: Criminal Justice and Offender Management
element.documentation: Refers to the delivery of justice to those that have committed crimes or offences.

element.name: Law Commission
element.documentation: Reviews existing laws and recommends potential for reform if necessary.

element.name: Police Authority
element.documentation: Consists of activities that co-ordinate law enforcement services.

element.name: Police Complaints
element.documentation: Handles the assessment of dissatisfaction with a police force or individual to maintain public confidence.

element.name: Prison Monitoring
element.documentation: Represents the monitoring of facilities used to detain criminal offenders.

element.name: Youth Offending
element.documentation: Oversees young offenders and provisions community services to prevent young people recommitting crimes in the future.

element.name: Financial
element.documentation: The Financial sector maintains controls over public spending, revenue, financial reporting, auditing, and providing the direction for future investment decisions and financial planning.

element.name: Import Duty
element.documentation: The collection of taxes on imports and some exports by customs authorities.

element.name: Revenue
element.documentation: Activities associated with the collection of money owed to the government from domestic and foreign sources.

element.name: Social Security
element.documentation: Promotes the welfare of the population through assistance measures to help in case of instability of living and to prevent such instability.

element.name: Tax and Revenue Compliance
element.documentation: Supports individuals and businesses towards compliance with taxation requirements and surrendering of taxes and levies to the government.

element.name: Tax Office
element.documentation: Responsible for the administration of the tax system, tax policy development, maintenance, and implementation.

element.name: Corporate and Business Planning
element.documentation: Examines internal capabilities and lays out strategies for how to use those capabilities to meet goals.

element.name: Financial Planning
element.documentation: Assesses the long-term fiscal needs of the government and acquires, allocates resources, and manages costs.

element.name: Investment Decisions
element.documentation: Determines where and how much capital will be spent on investment opportunities.

element.name: Policy Support
element.documentation: Assesses the sustainability of current programs and policies.

element.name: Strategic Finance
element.documentation: Activities pertaining to delivering long-term financial strategies to support future service delivery, financial monitoring, and control.

element.name: Strategic Risk
element.documentation: Analyzes exposure to risk and determines appropriate measures to ensure continued activities.

element.name: Accounting and Reporting
element.documentation: Activities to identify, organize, classify, record, summarize, and communicate information of financial transactions.

element.name: Accounting Standards Compliance
element.documentation: Ensures that accounting information is uniform and accounting decisions are made in a reasonable way.

element.name: Finance Business Partnering
element.documentation: Manages business partnerships and relationships between businesses, organizations, and individuals that contribute to the government’s objectives.

element.name: Finance Planning and Performance
element.documentation: Defines the set of capabilities to measure the effectiveness of a government’s financial assets and capital.

element.name: Cash Management
element.documentation: The process of collecting and managing cash flows.

element.name: Investment Management
element.documentation: Refers to the handling of financial assets and other investments.

element.name: Investments
element.documentation: Monetary assets acquired with the goal of generating income in the future.

element.name: Pension Fund Management
element.documentation: About investing and managing pension fund assets to optimize contributions made into that pension fund.

element.name: Shareholders of Owned Subsidiaries
element.documentation: Refers to shares in a company owned or controlled by a parent company.

element.name: Enterprise Risk
element.documentation: Identifies and addresses the potential events that represent risks to the achievement of strategic objectives.

element.name: Financial Governance
element.documentation: Collects, manages, monitors, and controls financial information.

element.name: Internal Audit
element.documentation: Provides independent assurance that a government’s risk management, governance, and internal control processes are operating effectively.

element.name: Risk and Audit
element.documentation: Methodical examination and review of regulated activities to ensure compliance with standards for regulated activity.

element.name: Growth, Housing, and Environment
element.documentation: Growth, Housing, and Environment corresponds to activities that ensure natural and urban environment responsibility, provision of core infrastructure, and protection of citizens’ standards of living and safety through the licensing and enforcement of regulation.

element.name: Business and SME Support
element.documentation: Provides support systems to small and medium-sized enterprises and businesses.

element.name: Culture
element.documentation: Pertains to activities that support development and management of the arts and cultural organizations, such as museums, galleries, and artifacts.

element.name: Electricity
element.documentation: Refers to the activities that support industry partnerships, and advises on regulations and standards associated with electricity usage and power.

element.name: Grants
element.documentation: Refers to the provision of loans in order to assist with funding partners.

element.name: Partnership
element.documentation: Relationships between two or more functions.

element.name: Port
element.documentation: Refers to the activities that support industry partnerships and adequate regulation of maritime ports.

element.name: Post
element.documentation: Refers to the activities that support the collection and delivery of packages and letters, issues postage stamps, and advises on regulations and standards associated with mail.

element.name: Rural Economy
element.documentation: Encompasses activities associated with the development, investment, and regulation of nature, agricultural activities, and the human environment.

element.name: Sport
element.documentation: Encompasses activities required to maintain, run, and advise on regulations for recreational and sporting facilities.

element.name: Telecommunications
element.documentation: Involves the support of telecommunications organizations that transmit signals and advises on regulations, standards, and new technology associated with telecoms.

element.name: Tourism
element.documentation: Encourages recreational visitors to the area, supports the tourism industry, and advises on tourism regulations.

element.name: Water
element.documentation: Refers to the activities that support water industry partnerships, and advises on regulations and standards associated with water management and usage.

element.name: Environmental Ecology
element.documentation: Refers to activities to modify a habitat to a better state, protect ecosystems, and support conservation.

element.name: Environmental Services
element.documentation: Refers to the maintenance, safeguarding, and provision of advice in order to preserve the natural environment.

element.name: Marine and Fisheries
element.documentation: Carries out maintenance and promotes community awareness of sea-based areas of the natural environment.

element.name: Meteorological Services
element.documentation: Involves the provision of advice, information, and warnings about the climate, weather forecasts, and severe weather.

element.name: Natual Environment
element.documentation: The management and conservation of the surrounding environment and wildlife to protect and ensure sustainability of the natural environment.

element.name: Veterinary Services
element.documentation: Refers to advice and research provided to ensure good health of domestic animals.

element.name: Architects
element.documentation: Encompasses the activities associated with the planning, design, and construction of properties and buildings.

element.name: Asset Management
element.documentation: Accounts for support for the management of government assets.

element.name: Capital Projects
element.documentation: Refers to the support, development, and management of long-term investment projects.

element.name: Property
element.documentation: Pertains to activities that support, develop, and manage buildings.

element.name: Property and Special Projects
element.documentation: Delivers investment and management services for development and infrastructure projects.

element.name: Surveying
element.documentation: Refers to the valuation, costing, management, marketing, and maintenance of public property and buildings.

element.name: Building Control
element.documentation: Determines the minimum standards required for design and construction.

element.name: Document Verification Service
element.documentation: Verifies key government issued documentation to ensure adherence to legislation and mitigate fraud.

element.name: Environmental Health
element.documentation: Advises and evaluates the effects of industry, tourism, or community use on the natural environment.

element.name: Environmental Protection
element.documentation: Refers to activities associated with the correcting and offsetting of environmental deficiencies.

element.name: Licensing
element.documentation: Refers to activities associated with granting, revoking, and management of the documented authority required to perform a regulated task or function.

element.name: Regulation
element.documentation: Refers to the delivery of regulatory processes.

element.name: Trading Standards
element.documentation: Refers to the enforcement of legislation associated with partnerships to ensure protection of consumers.

element.name: Policy, Performance, Population, and Innovation
element.documentation: Policy, Performance, Population, and Innovation involves the development of policy across the government, the provision of statistics for population and performance against benchmarks to ensure continuous improvement, and incorporates strategic and long-term planning to identify future risks, opportunities, and solutions.

element.name: Collaborative Policy
element.documentation: Refers to activities that monitor, manage, and respond to the wants and meets of the marketplace.

element.name: Economic Policy
element.documentation: Encompasses activities, guidelines, principles, and legislation administered by the government in order to analyze economic stability and growth.

element.name: Environmental Policy
element.documentation: Encompasses activities, guidelines, principles, and legislation administered by the government in order to minimize the environmental effects of society.

element.name: Policy
element.documentation: Develops and assesses the sustainability of current programs and policies that pertain to the environment, society, economy, and marketplace.

element.name: Policy Secretariat
element.documentation: Co-ordinates the analysis, needs assessment, and initiation of the drafting of strategic documents to establish public policies and streamline policy procedures.

element.name: Social Policy
element.documentation: Refers to activities, guidelines, principles, and legislation administered by the government to reduce inequality and ensure adequate welfare.

element.name: Capacity Planning
element.documentation: Refers to activities used to determine the maximum amount of change and production capacity the government has available in order to meet planning requirements.

element.name: Key Performance Indicators
element.documentation: Measures outcomes and activities to ascertain the success of the government by achieving strategic objectives and determining improvement criteria.

element.name: Planning and Performance
element.documentation: Refers to the continuous process of identifying and planning the best way to reach goals.

element.name: Population Statistics (and Census)
element.documentation: Comprises generating population statistics and census, including monitoring population trends and benchmarks to inform research, policy-making, and planning.

element.name: Economic Strategy
element.documentation: Refers to plans, initiatives, and activities used to achieve economic goals and enhance performance through more efficient allocation and utilization of resources.

element.name: Environmental Strategy
element.documentation: Refers to plans, initiatives, and activities used to achieve environmental goals and tackle climate change.

element.name: Housing Strategy
element.documentation: Refers to plans, initiatives, and activities used to achieve housing goals and promote flexibility and affordability of housing.

element.name: Innovation and Strategy
element.documentation: Refers to plans, initiatives, and activities used to achieve goals, address unmet market needs, and utilize emerging technology to do so.

element.name: Long-Term Strategy
element.documentation: Comprises the determination of strategic goals and the identification of the best method to achieve goals.

element.name: Population Strategy
element.documentation: Refers to plans, initiatives, and activities used to achieve population goals and address risks.

element.name: Short, Medium-Term Strategy
element.documentation: Comprises the determination of annual and near-terms goals and the identification of the best method to achieve goals.

element.name: Social Strategy
element.documentation: Refers to plans, initiatives, and activities used to achieve social goals and address social inequalities.

element.name: Shared Services
element.documentation: Shared Services co-ordinates and manages people, communications, finance, and transformation services on behalf of the public in order to facilitate the transfer of information and oversight of people, processes, and technology to support procurement and align to corporate strategy.

element.name: Business Administration Support
element.documentation: Refers to all activities that involve overseeing and supervising business operations.

element.name: Business Continuity
element.documentation: Involves the creation of systems in order to deter potential threats.

element.name: Compliance
element.documentation: Refers to the direct monitoring and oversight of people guidelines and regulations.

element.name: Culture and Modernization
element.documentation: Refers to activities used to update people services and manage employee culture.

element.name: Employee Health and Safety
element.documentation: Consists of activities used to design, develop, and implement employee health and safety programs.

element.name: Human Resources
element.documentation: Refers to activities associated with the management of employees including hiring, training, and communication.

element.name: People and Corporate Services
element.documentation: Activities that combine or consolidate people and enterprise-wide needed support services.

element.name: People and Organizational Change
element.documentation: Encompasses the processes that surround altering the government’s strategy, processes, culture, and technology.

element.name: Soft Facilities Management
element.documentation: Refers to the management of non-essential facilities to make the workplace more comfortable and enjoyable.

element.name: Communications
element.documentation: Growth, provision, and management of information, regulation, and media services to support the provision of communication services.

element.name: External Media
element.documentation: Refers to the movement of information between the government and the external environment.

element.name: Internal Communications
element.documentation: The regulation, growth, and management of industries that enable the transmission of information to domestic citizens.

element.name: International Communications
element.documentation: The regulation, growth, and management of industries that enables the transmission of information abroad.

element.name: Marketing
element.documentation: The provision of content and presentation of marketing material distributed through any medium.

element.name: Web Design
element.documentation: Refers to the design of interactive web content.

element.name: Commercial Negotiations
element.documentation: The identification, management, and conduct of strategic discussions to develop new opportunities.

element.name: Commercial Services
element.documentation: Activities related to sourcing, managing, and procuring contracts with vendors, suppliers, partners, and third parties to enable the development of new projects and opportunities.

element.name: Contract Management
element.documentation: The creation, execution, and analysis of contracts with partners and suppliers.

element.name: Market Creation
element.documentation: Refers to the elimination of trade barriers and provision of property rights to allow the development of a market for a good or service.

element.name: Market Engagement
element.documentation: Refers to the activities by which the government engages with suppliers prior to procurement of a project.

element.name: Procurement
element.documentation: Refers to the assessment of risk, evaluation of alternative options, award of contract to a supplier. and ongoing management of contracts for a product or service.

element.name: Business Processes
element.documentation: Refers to the monitoring, assessment, and enhancement of existing business processes, activities, and functions.

element.name: Data Protection
element.documentation: Activities associated with the protection, collection, compliance, and distribution of personal data.

element.name: Digital Government
element.documentation: Refers to the use of information and technology to provide digital offerings.

element.name: Enterprise Architecture
element.documentation: Activities used to define current, transition, and target strategies for an organization’s processes, people, and technology.

element.name: Information Management
element.documentation: Refers to activities that facilitate collection and migration of data and information.

element.name: Information Security
element.documentation: Refers to the protection of information and systems from unauthorized access, use, modification, or destruction.

element.name: IT Operations
element.documentation: Comprises processes and services administered by the IT department.

element.name: Portfolio and Performance Management
element.documentation: Supports the administration and effectiveness of investments and assets held by the government.

element.name: Transformation
element.documentation: The complete reassessment and overhaul of a function.

element.name: Analytics
element.documentation: All forms of data analysis from extremely large, complex data sets (Big Data) that are manipulated through to sparse rare-occurrence data.

element.name: Debt Management
element.documentation: The process of establishing and executing a strategy for managing debts, achieving risk and cost objectives, and meeting any other debt management goals set.

element.name: Finance Hub
element.documentation: Financial center whereby a large number and variety of financial services institutions are headquartered.

element.name: Payroll
element.documentation: The total compensation to be paid to employees for a set period of time.

element.name: Pension Fund Administration (PFA)
element.documentation: Responsible for opening Retirement Savings Accounts (RSA), the payment of retirement benefits, and accounting for all transactions relating to pension funds.

element.name: Reporting
element.documentation: Includes provision of financial information, reporting, and analysis of financial transactions.

element.name: Standardized Processes
element.documentation: Establishes a set of validated and accepted procedures that define appropriate and reliable practices.

element.name: Transactional Services
element.documentation: Oversees business transactions and deals such as mergers or acquisitions.

element.name: Transport and Operations
element.documentation: Transport and Operations includes activities that enable general operations including maintenance and general management, and guarantee the safe transfer and availability of people and goods over land, air, sea and space.

element.name: Air Transport
element.documentation: Involves the activities to ensure safe transfer and availability of people and goods through air.

element.name: Ground Transport
element.documentation: Involves the activities to ensure safe transfer and availability of people and goods over land.

element.name: Other Transport
element.documentation: Involves all other movement of people and goods not covered by land, air, water, and space through latitude and longitude.

element.name: Space Transport
element.documentation: Involves the activities to ensure safe transfer and availability of people and goods in space.

element.name: Transport
element.documentation: Activities pertaining to the safe transfer and availability of people and goods over land, air, sea, and space.

element.name: Water Transport
element.documentation: Involves the activities to ensure safe transfer and availability of people and goods over water.

element.name: Car Parks
element.documentation: Refers to ensuring the security, upkeep, and maintenance of public car parks.

element.name: Operations
element.documentation: Activities pertaining to the maintenance and general management of waste, public property, greenery, parking facilities, and streets.

element.name: Parks and Trees
element.documentation: Refers to the maintenance, planting, and conservation of trees and greenery in national parks, public parks, and conservation areas.

element.name: Property Maintenance
element.documentation: Refers to ensuring the security, upkeep, and maintenance buildings and properties owned by the government.

element.name: Street Maintenance and Highways
element.documentation: Refers to the repair, upkeep, and maintenance of roads, footways, and highways.

element.name: Waste Management
element.documentation: Corresponds to the disposal, recycling, monitoring, collection, or movement of waste.
